      • BATCH_UPDATES

        public static final DB.Option BATCH_UPDATES
        Batch updates (enabled initially by default). This should provide better performance for row insertion when using JDBDT.insert(DataSet) and JDBDT.populate(DataSet). The option has no effect though if the database driver does not support batch updates (as indicated by DatabaseMetaData.supportsBatchUpdates().

      • CASE_SENSITIVE_COLUMN_NAMES

        public static final DB.Option CASE_SENSITIVE_COLUMN_NAMES
        Handle column names in case-sensitive manner. This is required if you wish to use double-quotes with column names, by default JDBDT will handle column names in case-insensitive manner. This support may be fragile for some database engines.
        Since:
        1.1
